draw(B--H--C,dashed);
draw(D--J--Ep,dashed);
draw(F--G--A,dashed);

label("$A$",A,S);
label("$B$",B,S);
label("$C$",C,NW);
label("$D$",D,NW);
label("$E$",Ep,NE);
label("$F$",F,NE);
label("$G$",G,SE);
label("$H$",H,SW);
label("$J$",J,N);

label("$1$",(A+B)/2,N);
label("$7$",(B+C)/2,NE);
label("$2$",(C+D)/2,SE);
label("$4$",(D+Ep)/2,S);
[/asy] The answer is 9.

Rotating $360^\circ$ is the same as doing nothing, so rotating $600^\circ$ is the same as rotating $600^\circ - 360^\circ = 240^\circ$.  Therefore, we have $\sin 600^\circ = \sin (600^\circ - 360^\circ) = \sin 240^\circ$.

